## ERROR TIPS

### Errors when using extracting but being too far
 -  Make sure to move to the target entity where you want to extract from before extracting items

### Errors when placing into a tile which is occupied by another entity
- Ensure you can place a entity to a tile before attempting placing

### Errors when crafting items with missing ingredients
- Ensure you have all the ingredients required to craft an item before attempting to craft it. The error message specifies which item is missing.

### Errors when extracting items
- "Could not extract" errors can occur when the target entity does not contain the item you are trying to extract, or when the quantity you are trying to extract exceeds the available quantity.

### Errors when inserting items
- "Could not insert: LuaItemStack" errors can occur when the target entity's inventory is full.

### Errors when crafting items
- "attempt to concatenate local error_msg (a nil value)" errors can occur when crafting items.
